atiSwitchMib.name: atiSwitchMib
atiSwitchMib.description: Private MIB for ATI next generation layer 2 switches. This MIB can be used in Windows and UNIX environment

atiswitchProductType.name: atiswitchProductType
atiswitchProductType.description: This object identifies the Product Type.

atiswitchBasePortCount.name: atiswitchBasePortCount
atiswitchBasePortCount.description: This object determines the number of base Ethernet ports in the switch.

atiswitchUplinkPortCount.name: atiswitchUplinkPortCount
atiswitchUplinkPortCount.description: This object determines the total number of uplink ports available in the switch.

atiswitchReset.name: atiswitchReset
atiswitchReset.description: Setting this object to switchreset will cause the switch to perform a soft reboot. Setting this object to switch_no_reset will have no effect.

atiswitchUplink1Type.name: atiswitchUplink1Type
atiswitchUplink1Type.description: This object returns the MDA (Media Dependant Adapter) type of Uplink port 1. If there is no uplink installed it will return a value of none.

atiswitchUplink2Type.name: atiswitchUplink2Type
atiswitchUplink2Type.description: This object returns the MDA (Media Dependant Adapter) type of Uplink port 2. If there is no uplink installed it will return a value of none.

atiswitchSw.name: atiswitchSw
atiswitchSw.description: Identifies the name of the software running in the switch.

atiswitchSwVersion.name: atiswitchSwVersion
atiswitchSwVersion.description: Identifies the version number of the software running in the switch.

atiswitchIPAddressStatus.name: atiswitchIPAddressStatus
atiswitchIPAddressStatus.description: The IP Address can be obtained/configured through different ways - through DHCP, through Bootp or through a static configuration. This object specifies how the IP address, subnet mask and the gateway address currently used by the switch was configured/obtained.

atiswitchDNServer.name: atiswitchDNServer
atiswitchDNServer.description: This attribute specifies the DNS server address for the switch.

atiswitchDefaultDomainName.name: atiswitchDefaultDomainName
atiswitchDefaultDomainName.description: This attribute specifies the default Domain Name for the switch.

atiswitchNwMgrTable.name: atiswitchNwMgrTable
atiswitchNwMgrTable.description: This table contains the list of IP Addresses (management stations) to which SNMP Traps are sent. The maximum number of entries in the table is 4.

atiswitchNwMgrEntry.name: atiswitchNwMgrEntry
atiswitchNwMgrEntry.description: An entry of atiswitchNwMgrTable specifying each management station to which a SNMP trap is sent.

atiswitchNwMgrIndex.name: atiswitchNwMgrIndex
atiswitchNwMgrIndex.description: The index for the management station entry.

atiswitchNwMgrIpAddr.name: atiswitchNwMgrIpAddr
atiswitchNwMgrIpAddr.description: The IP address of the management station.

atiswitchMirrorState.name: atiswitchMirrorState
atiswitchMirrorState.description: If the attribute is set to one of the first three values, then port mirroring is enabled. If disabled, port operation works nomally. No traffic gets mirrored.

atiswitchMirroringSourcePorts.name: atiswitchMirroringSourcePorts
atiswitchMirroringSourcePorts.description: This attribute identifies the source ports which are mirrored. All packets received, transmitted or both on these ports gets mirrored on to the destination port. It's value can be a single port number or a contiguous range of ports (eg. 1-5). This attribute will have an empty string when port mirroring is disabled.

atiswitchMirroringDestinationPort.name: atiswitchMirroringDestinationPort
atiswitchMirroringDestinationPort.description: This attribute identifies the destination port number which mirrors the source port. All packets received, transmitted or both on the source port gets mirrored on to this port. This attribute will have the value 0 when port mirroring is disabled.

atiswitchSecurityConfig.name: atiswitchSecurityConfig
atiswitchSecurityConfig.description: This attribute is a port security configuration object. Setting the value to 'disabled' will allow the switch to learn new MAC addresses as they come in. In enabledLearningLocked mode, the device will stop learning new addresses and the old addresses that the device has learned will be locked. In enabledLimited mode, only a limited number of addresses will be learned. In enabledSecured mode, the administrator is responsible for entering the MAC addresses manually. By doing this, the administrator knows exactly who is connecting to the switch.

atiswitchSecurityAction.name: atiswitchSecurityAction
atiswitchSecurityAction.description: This attribute identifies the security action taken in case of an intruder detected.

atiswitchPortTable.name: atiswitchPortTable
atiswitchPortTable.description: This table contains all the type of devices supported by this MIB.

atiswitchPortEntry.name: atiswitchPortEntry
atiswitchPortEntry.description: The device type in the DeviceTable.

atiswitchPortNumber.name: atiswitchPortNumber
atiswitchPortNumber.description: The object identifies the port of the switch.

atiswitchPortName.name: atiswitchPortName
atiswitchPortName.description: This attribute associates a user defined string name with the port.

atiswitchPortAutosenseOrHalfDuplex.name: atiswitchPortAutosenseOrHalfDuplex
atiswitchPortAutosenseOrHalfDuplex.description: This object allows an admin request to configure whether this port is set to autosense or one of the different speed/duplex combinations.

atiswitchPortLinkState.name: atiswitchPortLinkState
atiswitchPortLinkState.description: This attribute allows an admin request to read the status of link state on this port.

atiswitchPortDuplexStatus.name: atiswitchPortDuplexStatus
atiswitchPortDuplexStatus.description: This object allows an admin request to read the status of Duplex on this port.

atiswitchPortSpeed.name: atiswitchPortSpeed
atiswitchPortSpeed.description: This attribute allows an admin request to read the speed of this port.

atiswitchPortState.name: atiswitchPortState
atiswitchPortState.description: This attribute allows an admin request to disable or enable communications on this port. It also responds with the status of the port. Except enabled(1) and disabled(2), all values are read-only status.

atiswitchPortFlowControlConfig.name: atiswitchPortFlowControlConfig
atiswitchPortFlowControlConfig.description: This per port attribute determines whether the port has flow control enabled or not. By default, flow control is disabled.

atiswitchPortBackPressureConfig.name: atiswitchPortBackPressureConfig
atiswitchPortBackPressureConfig.description: This per-port attribute describes whether the port identified has Back Pressure Enabled or not.By default, Back Pressure is Disabled.

atiswitchPortVlanTagPriorityConfig.name: atiswitchPortVlanTagPriorityConfig
atiswitchPortVlanTagPriorityConfig.description: This per-port attribute allows the configuration of the Tag Priority to be Override or use the Tag Priority. By Default, all ports use Vlan Tag priority.

atiswitchPortCOSPriorityConfig.name: atiswitchPortCOSPriorityConfig
atiswitchPortCOSPriorityConfig.description: This per-port attribute allows the configuration of the priority of the port. There are 8 priorities as per the IEEE standard with 0 being the lowest priority and 7 the highest. In a switch environment, ports with higher priority has it's to and from traffic given higher priority when compared with those with lower priority.

atiswitchPortBroadcastConfig.name: atiswitchPortBroadcastConfig
atiswitchPortBroadcastConfig.description: This per-port attribute determines if broadcast packets received should be discarded or processed. By default, they will be processed.

atiswitchPortReset.name: atiswitchPortReset
atiswitchPortReset.description: This per-port attribute resets the port to the original default configuration.This can prove useful in situations where a port is experiencing a problem making a valid connection to the end node. Setting the value to 'no-reset' has no effect.

atiswitchBasicVlanTable.name: atiswitchBasicVlanTable
atiswitchBasicVlanTable.description: Table of Virtual LANs configured in the switch.

atiswitchBasicVlanEntry.name: atiswitchBasicVlanEntry
atiswitchBasicVlanEntry.description: An entry describing the configured Virtual LAN.

atiswitchBeVlanIndex.name: atiswitchBeVlanIndex
atiswitchBeVlanIndex.description: Index of the Virtual LAN entry. Maximum number of Virtual LANs in 8024/8024GB is 32.

atiswitchBeVlanTagId.name: atiswitchBeVlanTagId
atiswitchBeVlanTagId.description: VId of the Virtual LAN as stored in the tag information header in accordance with 802.1q specification.

atiswitchBeVlanTaggedPortMask.name: atiswitchBeVlanTaggedPortMask
atiswitchBeVlanTaggedPortMask.description: List of tagged ports in the Virtual LAN.

atiswitchBeVlanUntaggedPortMask.name: atiswitchBeVlanUntaggedPortMask
atiswitchBeVlanUntaggedPortMask.description: List of untagged ports in the Virtual LAN.

atiswitchBeVlanMirrorPort.name: atiswitchBeVlanMirrorPort
atiswitchBeVlanMirrorPort.description: Port number on which all Virtual LAN traffic is mirrored on. By default the value is 0 indicating no port mirroring.

atiswitchBeVlanRowStatus.name: atiswitchBeVlanRowStatus
atiswitchBeVlanRowStatus.description: Indicates the status of this entry. This object is used to create, modify or delete Virtual LAN entries as per the RowStatus specification of SMIv2. There are two ways to create a Virtual LAN entry - CreateAndGo (Used when all objects of the entry are set at one go) and CreateAndWait (Used when individual objects are set independently). CreateAndGo method: Assign values to all objects of the Virtual LAN entry. Set this object to CreateAndGo(4). CreateAndWait method: Set this object to CreateAndWait(5). Set individual object entries. When all other entries are set, set this object to Active(1). To delete a Virtual LAN entry, set this object to destroy(6).

atiswitchPort2VlanTable.name: atiswitchPort2VlanTable
atiswitchPort2VlanTable.description: Table of per port Virtual LAN configuration.

atiswitchPort2VlanEntry.name: atiswitchPort2VlanEntry
atiswitchPort2VlanEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing per port Virtual LAN information.

atiswitchPvPortNumber.name: atiswitchPvPortNumber
atiswitchPvPortNumber.description: This object identifies the port on the switch.

atiswitchPvVlanName.name: atiswitchPvVlanName
atiswitchPvVlanName.description: This object identifies the Virtual LAN name to which the port belongs to.

atiswitchVlanMode.name: atiswitchVlanMode
atiswitchVlanMode.description: This object specifies the current VLAN mode. Setting this object to 'user-configured (1)' allows the manager to create, delete and modify VLANs using 'atiswitchBasicVlanTable'. Setting this object to 'multiple (2)' or 'multiple-802-1Q (3)'will result in the creation of predefined VLANs. Setting these values requires that the object 'atiswitchVlanUplinkVlanPort' also be set in the same SET request. Note that SET operations on any object under 'atiswitchBasicVlanTable' are not allowed in these two modes.

atiswitchVlanUplinkVlanPort.name: atiswitchVlanUplinkVlanPort
atiswitchVlanUplinkVlanPort.description: This object specifies the Uplink VLAN Port ID used while creating pre-configured VLANs. This object can be set to any valid Port ID present on the switch. Note that a SET operation on the object 'atiswitchVlanMode' to the value 'multiple (2)' or 'multiple-802-1Q (3)' should always be accompanied by a SET operation on this object in the same SET request. By default this object is set to 0 when 'atiswitchVlanMode' is set to 'user-configured (1)'.

atiswitchEthMonRxGoodFrames.name: atiswitchEthMonRxGoodFrames
atiswitchEthMonRxGoodFrames.description: The total number of good frames received on the switch.

atiswitchEthMonTxGoodFrames.name: atiswitchEthMonTxGoodFrames
atiswitchEthMonTxGoodFrames.description: The total number of good frames that has been transimitted by the switch.

atiswitchEthMonTxTotalBytes.name: atiswitchEthMonTxTotalBytes
atiswitchEthMonTxTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes transimitted from the switch.

atiswitchEthMonTxDeferred.name: atiswitchEthMonTxDeferred
atiswitchEthMonTxDeferred.description: The number of times a transmission attempt failed because of the medium being busy.

atiswitchEthMonTxCollisions.name: atiswitchEthMonTxCollisions
atiswitchEthMonTxCollisions.description: The total number of collisions detected while transmitting from the switch.

atiswitchEthMonTxBroadcastFrames.name: atiswitchEthMonTxBroadcastFrames
atiswitchEthMonTxBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of Transmit Broadcast Frames while switching.

atiswitchEthMonTxMulticastFrames.name: atiswitchEthMonTxMulticastFrames
atiswitchEthMonTxMulticastFrames.description: The total number of Transmit Multicast frames while switching.

atiswitchEthMonRxOverruns.name: atiswitchEthMonRxOverruns
atiswitchEthMonRxOverruns.description: The total number of Received Overrun Frames while switching.

atiswitchEthErrorCRC.name: atiswitchEthErrorCRC
atiswitchEthErrorCRC.description: The total number of CRC errors on received packets.

atiswitchEthErrorAlignment.name: atiswitchEthErrorAlignment
atiswitchEthErrorAlignment.description: The total number of packets received that has alignment errors.

atiswitchEthErrorRxBadFrames.name: atiswitchEthErrorRxBadFrames
atiswitchEthErrorRxBadFrames.description: The total number of bad frames received.

atiswitchEthErrorLateCollision.name: atiswitchEthErrorLateCollision
atiswitchEthErrorLateCollision.description: The number of times collision was detected in the switch.

atiswitchEthErrorTxTotal.name: atiswitchEthErrorTxTotal
atiswitchEthErrorTxTotal.description: Total number of errors resulting from transmit operations.

atiswitchEthPortMonTable.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTable
atiswitchEthPortMonTable.description: A list of statistics entry for each port.

atiswitchEthPortMonEntry.name: atiswitchEthPortMonEntry
atiswitchEthPortMonEntry.description: A colletion of statistics kept for a particular port.

atiswitchEthPortMonRxGoodFrames.name: atiswitchEthPortMonRxGoodFrames
atiswitchEthPortMonRxGoodFrames.description: The total number of good frames received on this port.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxGoodFrames.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxGoodFrames
atiswitchEthPortMonTxGoodFrames.description: The total number of good frames transmitted from this port.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxTotalBytes.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxTotalBytes
atiswitchEthPortMonTxTotalBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted from this port.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxDeferred.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxDeferred
atiswitchEthPortMonTxDeferred.description: This is the count of first time Transmission attempt which failed on an interface due to medium being busy.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxCollisions.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxCollisions
atiswitchEthPortMonTxCollisions.description: The total number of collisions while switching on an interface.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxBroadcastFrames.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxBroadcastFrames
atiswitchEthPortMonTxBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast frames transmitted from this port.

atiswitchEthPortMonTxMulticastFrames.name: atiswitchEthPortMonTxMulticastFrames
atiswitchEthPortMonTxMulticastFrames.description: The total number of multicast frames transmitted from this port.

atiswitchEthPortMonRxOverruns.name: atiswitchEthPortMonRxOverruns
atiswitchEthPortMonRxOverruns.description: The total number of over sized frames received on this port.

atiswitchEthPortErrorEntry.name: atiswitchEthPortErrorEntry
atiswitchEthPortErrorEntry.description: A collection of statistics kept for a particular port.

atiswitchEthPortErrorRxBadFrames.name: atiswitchEthPortErrorRxBadFrames
atiswitchEthPortErrorRxBadFrames.description: Total number of bad Frames received on this port.

atiswitchEthPortErrorTxTotal.name: atiswitchEthPortErrorTxTotal
atiswitchEthPortErrorTxTotal.description: Total number of errors resulting from transmit operations.

atiswitchFwdVlanTable.name: atiswitchFwdVlanTable
atiswitchFwdVlanTable.description: This table associates MAC addresses (as stored in the forwarding table of the switch) to the Virtual LAN to which it belongs.

atiswitchFwdVlanMACAddr.name: atiswitchFwdVlanMACAddr
atiswitchFwdVlanMACAddr.description: A MAC address from the forwarding table of the switch.

atiswitchFwdVlanVlanId.name: atiswitchFwdVlanVlanId
atiswitchFwdVlanVlanId.description: The Virtual LAN to which atiswitchFwdVlanMACAddr belongs to.

atiswitchFwdVlanAge.name: atiswitchFwdVlanAge
atiswitchFwdVlanAge.description: Current age of the MAC Address in the forwarding table - 0 indicates it is still active, 1 indicates that the address has aged out.

atiswitchFwdVlanStatus.name: atiswitchFwdVlanStatus
atiswitchFwdVlanStatus.description: Status of the MAC address - inactive (1): It is no longer valid e.g, it was learned and has since aged out, but has not yet been flushed from the table, active (2): Learned or statically assigned and currently in use and other (3): Neither of the other two.

atiswitchFwdVlanPort.name: atiswitchFwdVlanPort
atiswitchFwdVlanPort.description: Either the value 0, or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the atiswitchFwdVlanMACAddr has been seen. A value of 0 indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address.

atiswitchStaticMACTable.name: atiswitchStaticMACTable
atiswitchStaticMACTable.description: This tables lists MAC addresses lexicographically from the static table which binds MAC address to ports on the switch.

atiswitchStaticMACAddress.name: atiswitchStaticMACAddress
atiswitchStaticMACAddress.description: This object identifies the MAC address associated with Static MAC table.

atiswitchStaticMACPortNumber.name: atiswitchStaticMACPortNumber
atiswitchStaticMACPortNumber.description: This object identifies the port for which the MAC address is associated statically in the MAC Table.

atiswitchStaticMACEntryStatus.name: atiswitchStaticMACEntryStatus
atiswitchStaticMACEntryStatus.description: The status of this entry. The meanings of the values are: valid(1) : This entry is valid. invalid(2) : This entry is no longer valid, but has not yet been flushed from the table.

atiswitchFanStopTrap.name: atiswitchFanStopTrap
atiswitchFanStopTrap.description: Trap sent when an error in the fan operation is detected.

atiswitchTemperatureAbnormalTrap.name: atiswitchTemperatureAbnormalTrap
atiswitchTemperatureAbnormalTrap.description: Trap sent when the temperature of the switch is abnormal.
